---
title: Three-Cheese Tagliatelle Alfredo with Broccoli and Tuscan Herbs
description: Calling all dairy heads! This pasta has a triple dose of cheese to make it ultra-rich and velvety. Although we couldn’t go over-the-top without bringing in a wholesome veg like broccoli for balance. When you combine that creamy flavor, green goodness, and tender, twirl-able noodles, you’ve got a recipe for pasta-night success.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/three-cheese-tagliatelle-alfredo-629ed7d2.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/three-cheese-tagliatelle-alfredo-5b6e008330006c7e63239d72-d7a0d7f5.pdf
cuisine: Italian
nutrition:
  calories: 790 kcal
  fat: 50 g
  saturated fat: 23 g
  carbohydrates: 80 g
  sugar: 10 g
  protein: 34 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 600 mg
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/three-cheese-tagliatelle-alfredo-5b6e008330006c7e63239d72
time required: 25 minutes
---

Wash and dry all produce. Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Cut any
large @broccoli florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces. Trim, then thinly slice
@scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced), separating greens and whites. Mince
@garlic{2%clove}(minced).

Once water boils, add @tagliatelle{6%ounce} to pot. Cook ~{6%minutes}, then add
broccoli. Continue to cook until noodles are al dente and broccoli is just
barely tender, about ~{2%minutes}. Scoop out and reserve 1 cup cooking water,
then drain.

Return empty pot to stove over medium heat. Add a large drizzle of
@olive oil{2%teaspoon}, then stir in scallion whites, garlic, and
@Tuscan Heat Spice{1%tablespoon}. Cook until fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}, then
pour in ¾ cup reserved cooking water. Add @cream cheese{4%tablespoon},
stirring until well combined. Remove pot from heat and set aside for
~{1%minute} to cool.

Once mixture in pot has cooled slightly, add @yogurt{4%ounce},
@Italian Cheese Blend{½%cup}, half the @Parmesan Cheese{¼%cup}, @butter{2%tablespoon},
and a few pinches of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch} and stir until smooth.

Add tagliatelle and broccoli to pot with sauce and stir until well combined. If
sauce seems thick, add more of the reserved cooking water until everything is
covered in a loose but creamy coating. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide pasta between plates or bowls. Sprinkle with scallion greens and
remaining Parmesan and serve.